title: Chief Complaint
content: Left wrist pain after a trip and fall

title: HPI Spencer
content: The patient experienced a trip and fall on 6/21/25 while leaving Groundlings, resulting in left wrist pain that initially improved but worsened with increased humidity in Massachusetts. She underwent X-rays at urgent care showing no fractures and was diagnosed with a sprain.

title: Musculoskeletal
content: Mild tendon inflammation over the ECU tendon. Pain with pro-supination. Excellent range of motion overall.

title: Imaging Results
content: X-rays of the left wrist are normal.

title: Plan
content: Recommend trial of hand therapy. Recommend MRI for further evaluation. Return to clinic after MRI.
